snippet: The White House said Monday that more than five million people had signed up for private health insurance under President Obama’s health care law, an increase of about 800,000 in the last two weeks.
abstract: Obama administration reports that more than five million people have signed up for private health insurance under health care law, an increase of about 800,000 in last two weeks.
